{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Once you have added Markdown pages to your site, you are just one step away from being able to list your posts on a dedicated index page.</p>\n<h3 id=\"creating-posts\"><a href=\"#creating-posts\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating posts</h3>\n<p>As described <a href=\"/docs/adding-markdown-pages\">here</a>, you will have to create your posts in Markdown files which will look like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"md\">\n      <pre class=\"language-md\"><code class=\"language-md\">---\npath: &quot;/blog/my-first-post&quot;\ndate: &quot;2017-11-07&quot;\ntitle: &quot;My first blog post&quot;\n---\n\nHas anyone heard about GatsbyJS yet?</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id=\"creating-the-page\"><a href=\"#creating-the-page\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating the page</h3>\n<p>The first step will be to create the page which will display your posts, in <code class=\"language-text\">src/pages/</code>. You can for example use <code class=\"language-text\">index.js</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\">\n      <pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> PostLink <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"../components/post-link\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">IndexPage</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    allMarkdownRemark<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> edges <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> Posts <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> edges\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">filter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>edge <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">!</span>edge<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>frontmatter<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>date<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// You can filter your posts based on some criteria</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>edge <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>PostLink</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">key</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>edge<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>id<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">post</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>edge<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Posts<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> IndexPage</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id=\"creating-the-graphql-query\"><a href=\"#creating-the-graphql-query\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating the GraphQL query</h3>\n<p>Second, you need to provide the data to your component with a GraphQL query. Letâ€™s add it, so that <code class=\"language-text\">index.js</code> looks like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\">\n      <pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> graphql <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> PostLink <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"../components/post-link\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">IndexPage</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    allMarkdownRemark<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> edges <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> Posts <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> edges\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">filter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>edge <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">!</span>edge<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>frontmatter<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>date<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// You can filter your posts based on some criteria</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>edge <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>PostLink</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">key</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>edge<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>id<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">post</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>edge<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Posts<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> IndexPage\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pageQuery <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> graphql<span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`\n  query {\n    allMarkdownRemark(sort: { order: DESC, fields: [frontmatter___date] }) {\n      edges {\n        node {\n          id\n          excerpt(pruneLength: 250)\n          frontmatter {\n            date(formatString: \"MMMM DD, YYYY\")\n            path\n            title\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n`</span></span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id=\"creating-the-code-classlanguage-textpostlinkcode-component\"><a href=\"#creating-the-code-classlanguage-textpostlinkcode-component\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating the <code class=\"language-text\">PostLink</code> component</h3>\n<p>The only thing left to do is to add the <code class=\"language-text\">PostLink</code> component. Create a new file <code class=\"language-text\">post-link.js</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">src/components/</code> and add the following:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\">\n      <pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Link <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby-link\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">PostLink</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> post <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Link</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">to</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>post<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>frontmatter<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>path<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>post<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>frontmatter<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>title<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>post<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>frontmatter<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>date<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Link</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> PostLink</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>This should get you a page with your posts sorted by descending date. You can further customise the <code class=\"language-text\">frontmatter</code> and the page and <code class=\"language-text\">PostLink</code> components to get your desired effects!</p>","excerpt":"Once you have added Markdown pages to your site, you are just one step away from being able to list your posts on a dedicated index pageâ€¦","timeToRead":2,"fields":{"slug":"/docs/adding-a-list-of-markdown-blog-posts/","anchor":"adding-a-list-of-markdown-blog-posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Adding a List of Markdown Blog Posts"},"parent":{"__typename":"File","relativePath":"docs/adding-a-list-of-markdown-blog-posts.md"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/adding-a-list-of-markdown-blog-posts/"}}